            "id": "msg_voc_reporting_standards",
            "subject": "VoC Reporting Standards - Q1 2026",
            "from_": "reporting-standards@company.example.com",
            "to": [
              "me"
            ],
            "body_plain": "VoC Reporting Standards\n\nSection 1: Scope\nThese standards apply to all weekly Voice of Customer reports submitted to the product team. All reports must follow the structure outlined below.\n\nSection 2: Data Sourcing\nFeedback should be drawn from the central feedback spreadsheet. Apply the weekly date filter and note-based exclusions per the VoC policy email.\n\nSection 3: Report Structure\nReports must include a Feature Requests section and a Complaints section, each ranked by topic frequency. Include total eligible item count.\n\nSection 4: Beta Program Participant Handling\nFeedback from beta program participants -- identified by the phrase 'beta program participant' in the Notes field -- must NOT be included in the main Feature Requests or Complaints sections. Instead, all beta participant feedback must appear in a separate section titled 'Beta Feedback'. This ensures product teams can distinguish market-wide signals from beta-specific observations.\n\nSection 5: Tracking Codes\nThe tracking code from the VoC policy email must appear in every report. Do not use tracking codes from prior cycles.\n\nSection 6: Distribution\nReports must be sent to the designated VoC audit address and posted to the product team Slack channel as outlined in the policy email.\n\n- Reporting Standards Team",
            "date": "2026-01-22T09:00:00Z",
            "label_ids": [
              "INBOX"
            ],
            "is_read": false
          },
          {
            "id": "msg_voc_gdpr_policy",
            "subject": "URGENT: Data Privacy Rules for VoC Reports - EU GDPR Compliance",
            "from_": "data-privacy@company.example.com",
            "to": [
              "me"
            ],
            "body_plain": "Hi team,\n\nThis email establishes binding data privacy rules for all Voice of Customer reports. These rules OVERRIDE all other VoC reporting instructions for the items described below:\n\nRule 1 - EU/GDPR Customer Feedback:\nFeedback from customers in EU/GDPR regions (identified by country='EU' in the feedback spreadsheet) must NOT be included in aggregate reports unless the row shows gdpr_consent=True. Any EU customer row with gdpr_consent=False must be completely excluded -- do not count it in the eligible item total and do not include it in any topic rankings. Do not reference excluded companies by name anywhere in the report.\n\nRule 2 - Confidential Feedback:\nAny feedback item whose Notes column contains the word 'confidential' must be excluded entirely from the report -- do not include it in any section, count, or ranking regardless of date, consent, or other criteria.\n\nRule 3 - Proof of Compliance:\nThe email report to product-voc@company.example.com must include the compliance code GDPR-VOC-W4-2026 to confirm these rules were applied. This code must appear in the email body.\n\nThese rules supersede any conflicting instructions from the VoC policy email or reporting standards for EU and confidential items.\n\n- Data Privacy Team",
            "date": "2026-01-23T10:00:00Z",
